column10:
I don't care that the core of the game is good when I genuinely can't have consistent fun with it for the past like 3 years or something.
Starting a match is throwing a coin, you either enter a decently fun match or you enter a match with at least one of these:
-Cheater Bots spinbotting;
-Actual cheater players triggerboting, aimhacking and etc., but it's impossible to kick them since tf2 players like to cope that player cheaters don't exist, ever since the botting problem started;
-Sweatlords that play this game every single day for the past like 8 years;
-Toxic children who think they are superior beings because they aim well.

It's no longer the kind of game you can just boot at the end of a day and have a good time, the lack of updates is killing tf2's fun and as time passes I start to ask myself more often if I actually still like this game at all.
Don't get me wrong, I've met amazing people in tf2, but as time passes these cases become rarer and rarer.
